blem\n(or distance labeling) requires the algorithm to output the shortest\n\\emph{constrained} walk (or its distance) for a given source and sink vertices.\nWe show that this problem can be efficiently solved in the CONGEST model by\nreducing it to an \\emph{unconstrained} version of the problem.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 30 May 2022 07:32:58 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-05-31"}
