ity-independent R3Y NN potentials obtained for considered\nnon-linear NL1, NL3 and TM1 parameter sets. According to the present analysis,\nit is concluded that the NL1 and NL3 parameter sets provide comparatively\nbetter overlap with the experimental fusion and/or capture cross-section than\nthe TM1 and DDME2 parameter sets.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 30 May 2022 12:12:30 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-05-31"}
