{"id":"2205.15144","submitter":"Marat Rovinsky","authors":"M. Rovinsky","title":"Invariant fields of rational functions and semilinear representations of\n  symmetric groups over them","comments":"This is a preliminary version; supersedes arXiv:1405.3265 and\n  arXiv:1508.02267; v2: many modifications, all irreducible finite-dimensional\n  representations over `cross-ratio' fields are described","journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"math.RT math.AG","license":"http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/","abstract":"  Let $K$ be a field and $G$ be a group of its automorphisms endowed with the\ncompact-open topology. There are many situations, where it is natural to study\nthe category $Sm_K(G)$ of smooth (i.e. with open stabilizers) $K$-semilinear\nrepresentations of $G$. The category $Sm_K(G)$ is semisimple (in which case $K$\nis a generator of $Sm_K(G)$) if and only if $G$ is precompact. In this note we\nstudy the case of the non-precompact group $G$ of all permutations of an\ninfinite set $S$. It is shown that the categories $Sm_K(G)$ are locally\nnoetherian; the morphisms are `locally split'. Given a field $F$ and a subfield\n$k\\neq F$ algebraically closed in $F$, one of principal results describes the\nGabriel spectra (and related objects) of the categories $Sm_K(G)$ for some of\n$G$-invariant subfields $K$ of the fraction field $F_{k,S}$ of the tensor\nproduct over $k$ of the labeled by $S$ copies of $F$. In particular, the object\n$F_{k,S}$ turns out to be an injective cogenerator of the category $Sm_K(G)$\nfor any $G$-invariant subfield $K$ of $F_{k,S}$. As an application, when\ntranscendence degree of $F|k$ is 1, a correspondence between the $G$-invariant\nsubfields of $F_{k,S}$ algebraically closed in $F_{k,S}$ and certain systems of\nisogenies of `generically $F$-pointed' torsors over absolutely irreducible\none-dimensional algebraic $k$-groups is constructed, so far only in\ncharacteristic 0. The only irreducible finite-dimensional smooth representation\nof $G$ is trivial. However, there is an invariant `cross-ratio' subfield $K$ of\n$k(S)$ such that the irreducible finite-dimensional smooth $K$-semilinear\nrepresentations of $G$ correspond to the irreducible algebraic representations\nof $PGL_{2,k}$. In general, any smooth $G$-field $K$ admits a smooth $G$-field\nextension $L|K$ such that $L$ is a cogenerator of $Sm_L(G)$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 30 May 2022 14:40:15 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 27 Feb 2023 16:33:54 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-02-28"}
